ZH: 这是犯法的行为。
EN: This is a criminal behavior.

ZH: 他因为犯法而被逮捕。
EN: He was arrested for committing a crime.

ZH: 他犯法了，所以他被判刑了。
EN: He broke the law, so he was sentenced.

ZH: 每个人都应该遵守法律，而不是犯法。
EN: Everyone should abide by the law instead of committing crimes.

ZH: 如果你不想犯法，就要明白法律规定。
EN: If you don't want to break the law, you need to understand the legal provisions.

ZH: 犯法者将受到法律的制裁。
EN: Lawbreakers will be punished by the law.

ZH: 犯法行为会对社会造成不良影响。
EN: Criminal behavior will have a negative impact on society.

ZH: 我们应该向警方报告任何犯法行为。
EN: We should report any criminal activities to the police.

ZH: 根据法律，犯法是不允许的。
EN: According to the law, committing a crime is not allowed.

ZH: 犯法的人应该为自己的行为付出代价。
EN: People who commit crimes should pay for their actions.

ZH: 道德教育可以减少犯法行为的发生。
EN: Moral education can reduce the occurrence of criminal behavior.

ZH: 犯法是对社会的不负责任的表现。
EN: Committing a crime is an irresponsible behavior towards society.

ZH: 犯法行为将破坏人们的安全感。
EN: Criminal behavior will undermine people's sense of security.

ZH: 他犯法了，因此以后将面临很多麻烦。
EN: He committed a crime, so he will face a lot of trouble in the future.

ZH: 犯法行为是对他人权益的侵犯。
EN: Criminal behavior is an infringement on the rights of others.

ZH: 每个人都应该明白犯法的后果。
EN: Everyone should understand the consequences of breaking the law.

ZH: 犯法行为应该受到法律的制止和打击。
EN: Criminal behavior should be prevented and cracked down by the law.

ZH: 没有人愿意与一个犯法者为邻。
EN: No one wants to live next to a criminal.

ZH: 合理的法律可以降低犯法的发生率。
EN: Reasonable laws can reduce the occurrence of crimes.

ZH: 我们必须团结起来共同抵制犯法行为。
EN: We must unite together to resist criminal behavior.
